snippet.textDisplay:
I just went Dark blue and purple (was originally a nice Violet) and we didn't have the bleach that we usually use (professionally grade shiz) so my mom got box bleach... from Walmart. Yeah.... My hair went ginger first, with still some purple splotches from before, And then we had to apply some more, idk what type of bleach it was but it was weak. And then we went and foiled every part of my hair and colored it, It turned out surprisingly well despite the few mistakes my mom and I made, But I did notice that a little bit of my hair kept falling out (just various small strands) each time I showered, is that ok? And it feels a bit dry too. My mom told me to never condition the top of my head because it'll look bad but should I? And what should I use to recondition my hair? FYI I've got Naturally super thick hair, a lil longer than shoulder length and it's usually up in a ponytail, and I'm a natural brunette.

I hope you see this brad, or someone else who's more knowledgeable than me. Thank you. 😊

PLEASE PLEASE READ

https://www.gofundme.com/f/1vrqxqw9k0…

3 of my very close friends have unfortunately been in a two car collision Monday, January 27th, 2020. With originally non life threatening injures, to my knowledge, one of them is unconscious but he is breathing. As everyone prays all 3 will be okay, I thought of an idea and messaged one of my super close friends and soon began the plan. We want to raise money to help towards a new vehicle, as my friend, who is only 16 years old’s car is completely totaled. I believe insurance will help, but it will not make up for all the physical and emotional damage that has been done. Raising money to help for a new car for my close friend who I am so so grateful does not have any serious injuries, is the least I can do. Please, I encourage you to share this with everyone you know, as ANYTHING helps and will count. I am so sad things like this happen, but that’s the kind of world we live in.
